about.summary: High performance in-memory http request parser for application/json,  multipart/form-data, and application/x-www-form-urlencoded. Includes live demo of hosting and parsing multipart forms with either 'httpuv' or 'Rhttpd'.

name: r-webutils
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = '0.6' %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-webutils
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/webutils_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/webutils/webutils_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: fadaea7b20e00c756ab69ab456f55efe26abcc6f33443d0bb7c9a32af0a15aad

build:
  merge_build_host: True  # [win]
  number: 1001
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ compiler('c') }}        # [not win]
    - {{ compiler('m2w64_c') }}        # [win]
    - {{posix}}filesystem        # [win]
    - {{posix}}make
    - {{posix}}sed               # [win]
    - {{posix}}coreutils         # [win]
    - {{posix}}zip               # [win]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-curl >=2.5
    - r-jsonlite
  run:
    - r-base
    - {{native}}gcc-libs         # [win]
    - r-curl >=2.5
    - r-jsonlite

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('webutils')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('webutils')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://github.com/jeroen/webutils
  license: MIT
  summary: High performance in-memory http request parser for application/json,  multipart/form-data,
    and application/x-www-form-urlencoded. Includes live demo of hosting and parsing
    multipart forms with either 'httpuv' or 'Rhttpd'.
  license_family: MIT

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
    - johanneskoester
    - bgruening
    - daler
    - jdblischak
    - cbrueffer
    - dbast
